title: Densho Digital Archive
creator: Densho
description: Preserving and sharing stories of Japanese American incarceration during WWII. Densho collects video oral histories, photographs, documents, and newspapers. The archive is freely accessible online and has received national recognition for its community-based archival practices.
subject: Japanese American history; WWII incarceration; Oral history

title: Edwin T. Pratt Legacy Collection
creator: Black Heritage Society of Washington State
description: Photographs and materials honoring civil rights leader Edwin T. Pratt, documenting his legacy and the African American experience in Washington State. The organization holds one of the largest archives on Black history in the Pacific Northwest.
subject: Black history; Civil rights; Community heritage

title: Scarecrow Video Archive
creator: Scarecrow Video
description: Digitized materials from one of the world's largest publicly accessible video libraries, including rare and international media content. Scarecrow is a nonprofit dedicated to film preservation and education.
subject: Media preservation; Independent film; Community archives
